Wash and dry all produce. Core and seed @Poblano Pepper{1}, then cut into ½-inch
squares. Zest 1 tsp zest from @Lime{1}, then cut into quarters. Cut
@Chicken Thighs{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high
heat (use a nonstick pan if you have one). Add chicken and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned,
about ~{2%minutes}.

Add poblano to pan with chicken. Continue cooking until chicken is cooked
through and poblano is softened, about ~{5%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, core, halve, and dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Place in a #medium bowl{} and
set aside. Once chicken and poblano are done cooking, stir @Green Salsa{2%TBSP}
into pan. Add remaining @Green Salsa{5.06%ounce} to bowl with tomato and stir
to combine.

> The tomatillo-based salsa brings a pop of acidity and is a classic green
> salsa in Mexican cuisine.

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{6} in a lightly dampened #paper towel{} and microwave
until warm, ~{30-45%seconds}. In a #small bowl{}, stir together
@Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, lime zest, and 1 tsp lime juice.

Divide chicken and poblano mixture between tortillas. Spoon salsa and crema
over top. Sprinkle with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup}. Serve any remaining
lime quarters on the side for squeezing over.